place.name: TARRANT HINTON
place.gazetteerText: TARRANT-HINTON, a parish in Blandford district, Dorset; 5 miles NNE of Blandford r. station. Post town, Blandford. Acres, 2,279. Real property, £1,963. Pop., 258. Houses, 52. The living is a rectory in the diocese of Salisbury. Value, £370.* Patron, Pembroke College, Cambridge. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
